modules.description: Provides asynchronous operations for connecting to and interacting with Redis, including setting, getting, and deleting keys, as well as pub/sub messaging. Works with strings, byte sequences, and Redis-specific data types like hashes and lists. Used to build real-time applications requiring low-latency data retrieval and storage.

The module provides Redis-like operations for managing string, list, and set data structures, including bit manipulation (e.g., `getbit`, `setbit`), atomic increments, set algebra (e.g., union, intersection), and key management. It supports asynchronous key-value interactions, TTL adjustments, and connection lifecycle control, enabling use cases like real-time analytics, distributed caching, and data synchronization.
